===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|ls=psc|糸|韋|t1=thread|c1=s|c2=p}}. In earlier forms of {{lang|zh|韋}}, the components above and below {{lang|zh|囗}} were feet, each facing in opposite lateral directions (left and right).
(In this way, {{lang|zh|韋}} is also a semantic element representing horizontality.)

